        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-08T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/5–848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-08T17:00:00-06:00">May 8, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>206. In simple formal ceremony noon May 8 attended by diplomatic corps,
                    Archbishop, President elect Ulate, and new Supreme Court, Santos Leon Herrera
                    turned over power to founding Junta of second republic composed of José Figueres
                    as President of Junta without portfolio and Commander-in-Chief Army, Benjamín
                    Odio Foreign Minister, and Father Benjamín Nuñez Minister Labor. Other members
                    Cabinet are: Francisco Valverde Gobernación; Gonzalo Facio Justice; Edgar
                    Cardona Public Security; Uladislao Gámez Education; Alberto Martén Finance;
                    Francisco Orlich Public Works; Raúl Blanco Health; and Bruce Masís
                    Agriculture.</p>
                <p>New Supreme Court and other Justices sworn in.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
